%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20an%20Exploitative%20Labour%20Regime%20Doesn't%20Deter%20Rising%20Undocumented%20Migrants%20in%20the%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11111216%2FEffect-60.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20has%20long%20been%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%20for%20global%20migrants%2C%20attracting%20people%20from%20around%20the%20world%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20economic%20opportunity.%20However%2C%20beneath%20the%20surface%20of%20this%20migration%20phenomenon%20lies%20a%20complex%20interplay%20of%20economics%20and%20policy%2C%20particularly%20concerning%20undocumented%20migrants.%20These%20individuals%2C%20often%20unseen%20and%20under-discussed%20in%20the%20mainstream%20narrative%2C%20play%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20American%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20economy%20is%20characterised%20by%20high%20employment%20and%20significant%20gender%20parity%20in%20the%20workforce.%20Most%20American%20households%20have%20multiple%20earners%2C%20contributing%20to%20higher%20overall%20household%20income.%20Despite%20a%20long-term%20unemployment%20rate%20slightly%20above%205.5%25%2C%20the%20US%20maintained%20a%20low%20unemployment%20rate%20of%203.7%25%20in%202023.%20Concurrently%2C%20the%20long-term%20economic%20growth%20rate%20has%20been%20stable%2C%20approximately%20at%203.12%25.%20This%20robust%20economic%20performance%2C%20however%2C%20comes%20with%20its%20challenges%2C%20such%20as%20labour%20shortages%20in%20various%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMigration%20policies%20and%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20a%20complex%20yet%20effective%20set%20of%20migration%20policies%20and%20is%20a%20major%20destination%20for%20international%20students%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20join%20the%20American%20workforce%2C%20fulfilling%20the%20demand%20for%20educated%20and%20skilled%20labour.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20relies%20significantly%20on%20outsourcing%20technologically%20enabled%20tasks%2C%20particularly%20to%20China%2C%20India%2C%20and%20other%20developing%20economies.%20According%20to%20PEW%20Research%2C%20in%202017%20out%20of%2045%20million%20(13.7%25%20of%20population)%20immigrants%20in%20the%20US%2C%2010.5%20million%20were%20undocumented%2C%20making%20up%20about%203.2%25%20of%20the%20US%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20understand%20the%20glut%20in%20absolute%20numbers%20of%20illegal%20and%20undocumented%20immigrants%20in%20the%20US%20in%20association%20with%20the%20puzzle%20of%20US%20minimum%20wage%20rates.%20The%20minimum%20wage%20policy%20in%20the%20US%20is%20a%20contentious%20issue%2C%20with%20significant%20variations%20across%20states.%20The%20federal%20minimum%20wage%20stood%20at%20a%20modest%20%247.25%20per%20hour%20in%202023.%20However%2C%2030%20states%20have%20set%20higher%20minimum%20wages%2C%20with%20the%20highest%20being%20%2442%2C%20and%20the%20lowest%20at%20%2417%20per%20hour.%20The%20national%20average%20hovers%20just%20under%20%2426%20per%20hour.%20This%20disparity%20in%20wages%20is%20a%20key%20factor%20driving%20undocumented%20immigration%2C%20particularly%20across%20the%20southern%20US-Mexico%20border.%20It%20should%20also%20be%20noted%20that%20many%20illegal%20migrants%20and%20F1%20visa%20holders%20who%20work%20on%20the%20sly%20will%20get%20as%20low%20as%20%245%20per%20hour%20of%20work%2C%20making%20it%20the%20most%20exploitative%20labour%20force%20regime%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findians-detained-illegally-enter-us-border-data%5C%22%3ESince%202019%2C%201.49%20Lakh%20Indians%20Detained%20While%20Trying%20to%20Illegally%20Enter%20US%20Border%3A%20Data%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUndocumented%20immigration%20is%20an%20economic%20necessity%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20two%20major%20contesting%20political%20parties%20use%20this%20not%20only%20to%20politicise%20voting%20behaviour%20but%20also%20entice%20private%20investors%20and%20businesses%20which%20can%20do%20with%20an%20illiterate%20labour%20force.%20Thus%2C%20the%20influx%20of%20undocumented%20migrants%20is%20often%20a%20result%20of%20economic%20necessity%2C%20driven%20by%20the%20disparity%20in%20wage%20rates%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20labour%20in%20certain%20sectors.%20These%20immigrants%20find%20employment%20in%20infrastructure%2C%20hospitality%2C%20small%20businesses%2C%20and%20agriculture.%20Notably%2C%20they%20often%20receive%20formal%20documentation%20within%20months%20of%20arrival%20and%20can%20become%20naturalised%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20%E2%80%93%20a%20process%20significantly%20faster%20than%20for%20those%20on%20H1B%20and%20F1%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20impact%20on%20household%20economics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20US%20national%20residential%20rental%20average%20consuming%2030%25%20of%20median%20household%20income%20(and%20over%2050%25%20for%20the%20lowest%20income%20quintile)%2C%20individuals%20earning%20federal%20minimum%20wage%20or%20working%20unofficially%20face%20significant%20financial%20strain.%20Many%20immigrants%2C%20including%20the%20undocumented%2C%20take%20substantial%20risks%20to%20enter%20the%20US%2C%20motivated%20by%20the%20possibility%20of%20sending%20remittances%20back%20to%20their%20home%20countries.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20average%20daily%20wage%20in%20India%20is%20low%2C%20making%20even%20modest%20savings%20in%20the%20US%20significant%20enough%20to%20justify%20the%20risks%20of%20migration.%20Even%20the%20take-home%2C%20for%20example%2C%20of%20an%20Uber%20operator%20which%20can%20be%20as%20high%20as%20%244%2C000%20per%20month%20in%20the%20US%20is%20hovering%20around%20%24300%20(Rs%2025%2C000)%20per%20month%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffour-us-donkey-flights-had-left-for-nicaragua-when-french-immigration-intercepted-legend-airlines%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Wire%2520accessed%2520the%2520list%2Cto%2520Mumbai%2520on%2520December%252027.%5C%22%3EFour%20%E2%80%98US%20Donkey%20Flights%E2%80%99%20Had%20Left%20for%20Nicaragua%20When%20French%20Immigration%20Intercepted%20Legend%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUndocumented%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20typically%20earn%20a%20low%20of%20%241000%20per%20month%20(some%20also%20receive%20accommodation%20as%20part%20of%20their%20employment).%20The%20money%20sent%20back%20home%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20as%20little%20as%20%24300%20per%20month%20%E2%80%93%20translates%20into%20a%20substantial%20amount%20in%20Indian%20currency%2C%20providing%20considerable%20support%20to%20families%20in%20India.%20This%20economic%20incentive%20is%20a%20major%20factor%20driving%20migration%2C%20often%20through%20risky%20and%20illegal%20channels.%20Obvious%20that%20they%20reside%20in%20extremely%20rundown%20residential%20areas%20and%20even%20share%20a%20bed%20on%20a%20rotational%20basis.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20the%20immigrants%20(also%20undocumented)%20take%20risks%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20savings%20and%20remittances%20to%20their%20dependents%20back%20in%20their%20country%20of%20origin.%20Thus%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20a%20saving%20of%20%2410%20to%20%2420%20a%20day%20is%20enough%20to%20take%20extremely%20high-risk%20migrating%20routes%20even%20by%20paying%20high%20costs%20as%20evidenced%20by%20the%20recent%20example%20of%20a%20chartered%20plane%20from%20India%20to%20Nicaragua%2C%20which%20was%20stranded%20in%20France.%20It%20could%20also%20mean%20taking%20a%20life-threatening%20one-way%20trip%20in%20a%20shop%20container.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20speak%20over%20100%2C000%20Indians%20have%20entered%20the%20US%20through%20the%20%E2%80%98Dunki%E2%80%99%20routes%20which%20are%20well%20depicted%20in%20last%20week%E2%80%99s%20movie%20release%20of%20the%20same%20name%20produced%20by%20Rajkumar%20Hirani%20and%20acted%20by%20highly%20acclaimed%20acters%20%E2%80%93%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%2C%20Taapsee%20Pannu%2C%20and%20Vicky%20Kaushal.%20Illegal%20migration%20from%20India%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20happening%20from%20households%20that%20are%20poor%2C%20but%20rather%20from%20those%20which%20can%20afford%20to%20pay%20high%20fees%20for%20human%20traffickers%2C%20smugglers%2C%20and%20those%20dealing%20with%20hawala%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAbusaleh%20Shariff%20is%20with%20the%20US-India%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20Washington%20DC%2C%20and%20Centre%20for%20Research%20and%20Debates%20in%20Development%20Policy%2C%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Bengaluru.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704952062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11111216%2FEffect-60.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fwhy-an-exploitative-labour-regime-doesnt-deter-rising-undocumented-migrants-in-the-us%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22About%2010.5%20million%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20who%20made%20perilous%20journeys%20to%20reach%20the%20US%2C%20help%20run%20the%20American%20economy%20even%20working%20at%20an%20hourly%20rate%20as%20low%20as%20%245.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fwhy-an-exploitative-labour-regime-doesnt-deter-rising-undocumented-migrants-in-the-us%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20says%20his%20businesses%20got%20money%20from%20foreign%20governments%20because%20he%20was%20'doing%20services'%20for%20them%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224073%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659f7422dcdb354a985694e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222715%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20was%20accused%20of%20receiving%20at%20least%20%247.8%20million%20in%20foreign%20payments%20to%20his%20businesses%20during%20his%20presidency%2C%20per%20a%20report%20published%20by%20Democrats%20on%20the%20House%20Oversight%20Committee%20on%20January%204.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDonald%20Trump%20said%20his%20businesses%20were%C2%A0%26quot%3Bdoing%20services%26quot%3B%20for%20foreign%20countries%20during%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDemocrats%20recently%20accused%20Trump's%20businesses%20of%20receiving%20foreign%20payments%20while%20he%20was%20in%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20get%20%248%20million%20for%20doing%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20at%20a%20Fox%20News%20town%20hall%20on%20Wednesday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-donald-trump-bio-age-family-key-positions-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20his%20businesses%20received%20payments%20from%20foreign%20governments%20because%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bdoing%20services%26quot%3B%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20at%20a%20Fox%20News%20town%20hall%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20commenting%20on%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24253636-2024-01-04coa-dems-mazars-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20on%20the%20House%20Oversight%20Committee.%20The%20report%2C%20published%20on%20January%204%2C%20said%20Trump's%20businesses%20had%20received%20at%20least%20%247.8%20million%20in%20foreign%20payments%20during%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20money.%20You%20know%2C%20it%20sounds%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20That's%20small%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20at%20the%20town%20hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20then%20explained%20that%20the%20payments%20were%20for%20accommodation%20at%20his%20clubs%20and%20hotels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20doing%20services%20for%20them.%20People%20were%20staying%20in%20these%20massive%20hotels%2C%20these%20beautiful%20hotels%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20get%20%248%20million%20for%20doing%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%20from%20the%20Democrats%2C%20Trump's%20businesses%20had%20received%20payments%20from%20at%20least%2020%20countries%20while%20he%20was%20in%20office.%20Foreign%20governments%20and%20government-controlled%20entities%20had%20made%20payments%20to%20Trump's%20hotels%20in%20Washington%2C%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20and%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20ranged%20from%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20to%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo%20to%20Malaysia%20to%20Albania%20to%20Kosovo%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20countries%20spent%20%E2%80%94%20often%20lavishly%20%E2%80%94%20on%20apartments%20and%20hotel%20stays%20at%20Donald%20Trump's%20properties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20never%20sought%20or%20received%20Congress's%20approval%20to%20keep%20these%20foreign%20payments%2C%20as%20the%20Constitution%20requires%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20indicted%20in%20four%20separate%20prosecutions%20last%20year%20and%20faces%2091%20criminal%20counts%2C%20ranging%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-arraignment-pleads-not-guilty-new-york-indictment-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efalsifying%20business%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-read-charges-january-6-election-case-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_bl