family%20is%20stepping%20up%20in%20support%20of%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20new%20court%20documents%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20daughter%20claims%20in%20the%20docs%20that%20her%20father%20also%20was%20returned%20to%20the%20family%20without%20any%20organs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20family%20is%20claiming%20their%20son's%20organs%20went%20inexplicably%20missing%20after%20being%20incarcerated%20by%20the%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20(ADOC)%2C%20court%20documents%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20family%20of%20Brandon%20Clay%20Dotson%20sued%20the%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20after%20the%20son's%20body%20was%20returned%20without%20a%20heart%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%20Dotson%20died%20inside%20Ventress%20Correctional%20Facility%2C%20a%20state%20prison%2C%20in%20November%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDotson%20was%20returned%20to%20the%20family%20about%20five%20days%20after%20his%20death%20on%20November%2016%2C%202023%2C%20at%20the%20Ventress%20Correctional%20Facility%20%26quot%3Bseverely%20decomposed%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20Dotson%20family's%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20ordered%20a%20second%20autopsy%2C%20which%20is%20when%20the%20family%20was%20informed%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bheart%20was%20missing%20from%20the%20chest%20cavity%20of%20Mr.%20Dotson's%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20%E2%80%94%20or%20an%20agent%20responsible%20for%20conducting%20the%20autopsy%20or%20transporting%20the%20body%20to%20his%20family%20%E2%80%94%20had%2C%20inexplicably%20and%20without%20the%20required%20permission%20from%20Mr.%20Dotson's%20next%20of%20kin%2C%20removed%20and%20retained%20Mr.%20Dotson's%20heart%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20family%20alleged%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDotson's%20family%20has%20yet%20to%20find%20out%20what%20happened%20to%20their%20son's%20heart%20as%20the%20case%20remains%20open.%20And%20it%20appears%20a%20second%20family%20has%20stepped%20in%20to%20support%20their%20legal%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20documents%20show%20that%20Alabama%20resident%20Charlene%20Drake%20provided%20written%20testimony%20that%20claims%20her%20father's%20body%20was%20also%20returned%20to%20the%20family%20with%20missing%20organs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20did%20not%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20of%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrake's%20father%2C%20Charles%20Edward%20Singleton%2C%20was%2074%20when%20he%20died%20on%20November%202%2C%202021%2C%20while%20incarcerated%20by%20the%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%2C%20according%20to%20her%20testimony.%20He%20received%20care%20at%20%26quot%3Boutside%20hospitals%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20the%20Hamilton%20Aged%20and%20Infirmed%20Center%2C%20an%20ADOC%20facility%20that%20provides%20care%20for%20old%20inmates%2C%20the%20testimony%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chaplain%20of%20Hamilton%2C%20David%20Smith%2C%20called%20me%20on%20November%202%2C%20to%20tell%20me%20that%20my%20father%20Charles%20had%20died.%20Chaplain%20Smith%20said%20that%20ADOC%20could%20take%20care%20of%20the%20burial%20arrangements%2C%26quot%3B%20Drake%20wrote%20in%20the%20testimony.%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20him%20absolutely%20not%2C%20and%20that%20we%20wanted%20to%20claim%20the%20body.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20receiving%20an%20autopsy%2C%20Singleton%20was%20sent%20to%20a%20funeral%20home%20about%2040%20miles%20east%20of%20Birmingham%20for%20a%20family%20viewing.%20There%2C%20a%20funeral%20director%20would%20inform%20the%20family%2C%20about%20a%20week%20after%20Singleton's%20death%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20there%20were%20no%20organs%20in%20the%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20testimony%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20funeral%20director%20%26quot%3Bsaid%20normally%20the%20organs%20are%20in%20a%20bag%20placed%20back%20in%20the%20body%20after%20an%20autopsy%2C%20but%20Charles%20had%20been%20brought%20to%20the%20Funeral%20Home%20with%20no%20internal%20organs.%20His%20brain%20had%20also%20been%20removed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20testimony%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrake%20said%20in%20her%20written%20testimony%20that%20staff%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alabama%20at%20Birmingham%20(UAB)%2C%20where%20Singleton's%20autopsy%20was%20performed%2C%20never%20explained%20what%20happened%20to%20her%20father's%20organs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20UAB%20didn't%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20working%20hours.%20In%20a%20statement%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabc3340.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Ffamily-says-organs-including-brain-missing-from-deceased-inmate-body-in-noticeable-state-of-decomposition-adoc-uab-st-clair-county%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EABC%2033%2F40%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20UAB%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20%26quot%3Bpending%20litigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20an%20autopsy%2C%20organs%20and%20tissues%20are%20removed%20to%20best%20determine%20the%20cause%20of%20death.%20Autopsy%20consent%20includes%20consent%20for%20final%20disposition%20of%20the%20organs%20and%20tissues%3B%20unless%20specifically%20requested%2C%20organs%20are%20not%20returned%20to%20the%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20wrote%20to%20the%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Faraino%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20Dotson's%20family%2C%20did%20not%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20of%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Falabama-prisons-inmate-bodies-organs-missing-deaf18ac866955fdf4945e295c21dd46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Faraino%20wrote%20that%20the%20case%20Singleton's%20family%20shows%20that%20this%20is%20%26q