A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Freliance-jio-to-set-up-carbon-fibre-facility-at-hazira-in-gujarat-124011000669_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reliance%20Jio%20completed%20the%20fastest%20roll-out%20of%205G%20infrastructure%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Freliance-jio-to-set-up-carbon-fibre-facility-at-hazira-in-gujarat-124011000669_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Freliance-jio-to-set-up-carbon-fibre-facility-at-hazira-in-gujarat-124011000669_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Freliance-jio-to-set-up-carbon-fibre-facility-at-hazira-in-gujarat-124011000669_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Knowledge%20Production%20in%20Neo-Liberal%20Times%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F16173007%2FIMG_4643.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%E2%80%99s%20book%20Knowledge%20as%20Commons%3A%20Towards%20Inclusive%20Science%20and%20Technology%20published%20by%20LeftWord%20(2023).%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20transformations%20taking%20place%20today%20in%20educational%20institutions.%20One%20is%20to%20treat%20educational%20activity%20like%20any%20other%20business.%20The%20quantification%20of%20output%20in%20terms%20of%20teaching%20hours%2C%20students%E2%80%99%20performance%2C%20research%20papers%2C%20contributions%20to%20the%20income%20of%20the%20university%20from%20business%20and%20students%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98key%20performance%20indicators%E2%80%99%2C%20have%20become%20the%20yardstick%20for%20judging%20teachers%2C%20departments%2C%20and%20institutions.%20In%20this%20view%2C%20an%20educational%20institution%20should%20be%20treated%20like%20any%20other%20commercial%20activity.%20Its%20objective%20is%20to%20maximise%20output%E2%80%94in%20terms%20of%20more%20students%2C%20more%20patents%2C%20consultancies%2C%20research%20grants%E2%80%94while%20minimising%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20438px)%2085vw%2C%20438px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10175517%2F852657e5-b5a3-4364-8883-0870583e98ca.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22438%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10175517%2F852657e5-b5a3-4364-8883-0870583e98ca.jpg%20438w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10175517%2F852657e5-b5a3-4364-8883-0870583e98ca-192x300.jpg%20192w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692314%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22684%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrabir%20Purkayastha%2C%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EKnowledge%20as%20Commons%3A%20Towards%20Inclusive%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ELeftWord%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20transformation%20is%20the%20privatisation%20of%20the%20output%20of%20institutional%20research%2C%20even%20when%20publicly%20funded%20or%20funded%20by%20government%20grants.%20This%20generates%20more%20income%20for%20the%20university%2C%20while%20a%20still%20larger%20share%20of%20benefits%20flows%20to%20the%20corporations%20who%20are%20able%20to%20%E2%80%98enclose%E2%80%99%20the%20output%20by%20buying%20patents%20on%20the%20findings%20and%20applications%20of%20such%20publicly%20funded%20research.%20Such%20instances%20are%20most%20visible%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20pharmaceutical%20industry.%20They%20are%20facilitated%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20decision%20that%20the%20output%20of%20scientific%20or%20technological%20research%2C%20even%20if%20supported%20by%20the%20state%2C%20should%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20private%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20markets%20and%20the%20demands%20of%20global%20capital%20control%20science%20and%20its%20advances.%20Neither%20the%20objectives%20of%20advancing%20the%20knowledge%20system%2C%20nor%20those%20of%20meeting%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20people%2C%20are%20served%20by%20the%20current%20practice%20of%20science.%20Knowledge%2C%20and%20larger%20social%20goals%2C%20are%20sacrificed%20to%20the%20neoliberal%20economic%20order%20which%20values%20immediate%20gain%20as%20the%20driver%20of%20science.%20Science%20as%20an%20open%20system%2C%20at%20least%20among%20scientists%2C%20is%20giving%20way%20to%20the%20logic%20of%20capitalist%20enterprise.%20While%20we%20may%20talk%20about%20the%20knowledge%20economy%2C%20the%20output%20of%20scientific%20research%20has%20been%20privatised%2C%20even%20when%20publicly%20funded%20within%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20educational%20system.%20Before%20a%20result%20is%20published%2C%20scientists%20are%20already%20busy%20with%20establishing%20the%20claim%20to%20prior%20knowledge%20indispensable%20for%20filing%20patents.%20The%20output%20of%20scientific%20research%20no%20longer%20comprises%20research%20papers%20in%20journals%20that%20increase%20the%20boundaries%20of%20knowledge%2C%20but%20patents%20which%20can%20be%20turned%20into%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20led%20to%20a%20new%20goal%20within%20the%20scientific%20community%3A%20creating%20a%20new%20class%20of%20scientists%20who%20behave%20as%20entrepreneurs.%20They%20often%20operate%20within%20the%20public%20science%20institutions%2C%20but%20have%20become%20science%20entrepreneurs%20using%20the%20output%20of%20their%20research.%20The%20goal%20of%20research%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20production%20of%20knowledge%20but%20the%20creation%20of%20monopolies%20for%20either%20private%20capital%20or%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98scientist%20as%20entrepreneur%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonopoly%20over%20knowledge%2C%20whether%20used%20to%20sell%20a%20software%20program%2C%20a%20medicine%2C%20or%20a%20seed%2C%20translates%20into%20the%20ability%20to%20extract%20super%20profits.%20It%20also%20aborts%20the%20possibility%20of%20science%20being%20developed%20through%20an%20open%20network.%20It%20is%20paradoxical%20that%20while%20the%20internet%20and%20open%20access%20to%20knowledge%20have%20made%20it%20possible%20for%20large%20groups%20of%20people%20around%20the%20world%20to%20work%20together%20and%20bring%20about%20major%20advances%20in%20science%2C%20we%20are%20also%20witnessing%20a%20time%20in%20which%20knowledge%20is%20packed%20into%20cubbyholes%2C%20precluding%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20free%20software%20movement%20of%20the%201980s%20showed%20the%20power%20of%20new%20networked%20structures%20in%20creating%20software%2C%20and%20their%20superiority%20over%20privatised%20software%20development.%20Never%20before%20has%20society%20had%20the%20ability%20to%20bring%20together%20different%20communities%20and%20resources%20on%20this%20scale.%20We%20have%20seen%20what%20collaboration%20is%20capable%20of%20when%20harnessed%20to%20scientific%20activities%20such%20as%20particle%20physics%20or%20astronomy.%20So%2C%20what%20stands%20in%20the%20way%20of%20liberating%20this%20enormous%20power%20of%20working%20together%20for%20the%20generation%20of%20new%20knowledge%20and%20new%20artefacts%3F%20Clearly%2C%20the%20impediments%20are%20the%20monopoly%20rights%20and%20private%20appropriation%20inherent%20in%20the%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20(IPR)%20order.%20The%20understanding%20that%20science%20needs%20to%20be%20restored%20as%20an%20open%20and%20collaborative%20exercise%20has%20given%20birth%20to%20the%20commons%20movement.%20While%20the%20environmental%20and%20ecological%20movements%20have%20also%20fought%20against%20the%20privatisation%20of%20the%20commons%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20commons%20they%20looked%20at%20are%20finite%20resources%2C%20such%20as%20grazing%20land%2C%20forests%2C%20fisheries%2C%20oceans%2C%20and%20the%20atmosphere.%20These%20commons%20are%20natural%20resources%2C%20once%20thought%20to%20be%20infinite%2C%20and%20now%20understood%20to%20be%20finite%2C%20capable%20of%20over-exploitation%20and%20degradation.%20The%20knowledge%20commons%20are%20intrinsically%20different%20in%20that%20they%E2%80%94a%20law%20of%20nature%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20say%2C%20or%20knowledge%20of%20a%20genetic%20code%E2%80%94do%20not%20degrade%20with%20repeated%20use.%20Open%20use%20on%20a%20large%20scale%20enriches%20the%20knowledge%20commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fprabir-purkayastha-memoirs-harsh-mander-review%5C%22%3EPrabir%20Purkayastha%20Memoirs%3A%20An%20Unbroken%20Commitment%20to%20Rationalism%2C%20Scientific%20Temper%20and%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20%E2%80%98commons%E2%80%99%20view%20of%20the%20world%2C%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20are%20attempts%20to%20exclude%20people%20from%20the%20domain%20of%20knowledge%20by%20enclosing%20it%2C%20in%20a%20manner%20similar%20to%20the%20enclosure%20of%20the%20village%20commons%20carried%20out%20over%20the%20last%20500%20years.%20It%20uses%20a%20legal%20artifice%20called%20IPR%20to%20privatise%20knowledge%20that%20was%20always%20publicly%20held.%20Any%20enclosure%20of%20knowledge%20is%20doubly%20pernicious%3A%20it%20not%20only%20restricts%20access%20to%20others%2C%20but%20also%20puts%20a%20price%20on%20access%20to%20something%20which%20is%20infinitely%20duplicable%20and%20does%20not%20degrade%20with%20use.%20The%20enclosure%20of%20knowledge%20using%20the%20IPR%20regime%20is%20even%20more%20iniquitous%20than%20the%20earlier%20kind%20of%20enclosure%20movements%2C%20which%20had%20argued%20that%20private%20property%20rights%20prevented%20the%20degradation%20of%20the%20commons.%20The%20struggle%20against%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20of%20various%20kinds%20becomes%20a%20battle%20to%20preserve%20the%20global%20commons%2C%20specifically%20knowledge%20in%20its%20various%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20system%20of%20developing%20scientific%20knowledge%20resided%20primarily%20within%20the%20structures%20of%20higher%20education.%20Universities%2C%20colleges%2C%20and%20other%20institutions%20of%20higher%20learning%20were%20the%20centres%20where%20new%20advances%20in%20science%20originated.%20As%20these%20centres%20of%20education%20were%20relatively%20autonomous%20of%20both%20state%20and%20market%2C%20the%20system%20of%20generating%20new%20knowledge%20was%20not%20constrained%20by%20the%20immediate%20class%20needs%20of%20society.%20This%20produced%20within%20the%20university%20system%20a%20sense%20of%20independence%20and%20self-regulation%2C%20and%20the%20education%20given%20to%20students%20had%20a%20purpose%20larger%20than%20merely%20serving%20capital%20or%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20state.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20educational%20system%20became%2C%20additionally%2C%20a%20space%20where%20new%20ideas%20arose%20not%20only%20in%20the%20various%20disciplines%2C%20but%20also%20about%20society%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20humanist%20view%20of%20science%20and%20technology%20fitted%20very%20well%20within%20this%20overall%20structure.%20Science%20was%20supposed%20to%20produce%20new%20knowledge%2C%20which%20could%20then%20be%20mined%20by%20technology%20to%20produce%20artefacts.%20The%20role%20of%20innovation%20was%20to%20convert%20ideas%20into%20artefacts%E2%80%94thence%20the%20patenting%20system%20that%20provides%20protection%20to%20useful%20ideas%20embodied%20in%20the%20artefacts.%20Artefacts%20could%20be%20patented%2C%20but%20not%20knowledge%20of%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20transformation%20of%20this%20system%20after%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20years%20has%20come%20from%20two%20distinct%20sources.%20One%20is%20that%20science%20and%20technology%20are%20far%20more%20closely%20integrated%20than%20before%2C%20and%20scientific%20advances%20can%20be%20turned%20rapidly%20into%20marketable%20products.%20For%20example%2C%20advances%20in%20biology%20that%20create%20new%20pharmaceutical%20compounds%2C13%20or%20advances%20in%20physics%20entering%20the%20latest%20chip-%20making%20machines%2C14%20happen%20much%20faster%20today%20than%20they%20did%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20market%20fundamentalists%20the%20world%20over%20are%20pushing%20measures%20similar%20to%20the%20Bayh-Dole%20(Patent%20and%20Trademark%20Law%20Amendments)%20Act%2C15%20to%20enclose%20the%20advances%20in%20knowledge%20created%20by%20public%20funding.%20The%20Bayh-Dole%20Act%2C%20introduced%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%201980%2C%20reversed%20the%20almost%20universal%20assumption%20that%20public-funded%20research%20should%20not%20be%20protected%20by%20private%20rights%20in%20the%20form%20of%20intellectual%20property%20protection.%20The%20Act%20allowed%20universities%20and%20other%20non-profit%20entities%20to%20patent%20research%20funded%20from%20public%20resources.%20It%20created%20the%20conditions%20for%20the%20university%20system%20in%20the%20United%20States%20to%20work%20much%20more%20closely%20with%20large%20corporations.%20Publicly%20funded%20research%20can%20now%20be%20privatised%20by%20the%20university%2C%20by%20selling%20the%20patents%20to%20private%20corporations.%20The%20people%20pay%20twice%3A%20once%20for%20funding%20research%20with%20public%20money%2C%20and%20the%20second%20time%20by%20paying%20a%20high%20price%20for%20products%20developed%20from%20publicly%20funded%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20factors%20have%20also%20contributed%20to%20transforming%20the%20system%20of%20knowledge%20production%2C%20most%20notably%20the%20neoliberal%20policies%20adopted%20across%20the%20globe.%20Public%20funding%20on%20research%20has%20suffered%2C%20especially%20in%20developing%20nations%2C%20as%20neoliberal%20economics%20has%20led%20to%20a%20general%20squeeze%20on%20government%20finances.%20This%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20reliance%20on%20the%20market%2C%20has%20given%20rise%20to%20the%20notion%20that%20the%20way%20forward%20is%20to%20source%20research%20funding%20from%20the%20private%20sector.%20There%20is%20evidence%20today%20that%20private%20funding%20of%20research%20distorts%20the%20priorities%20upheld%20by%20public%20funding.%20Private%20companies%20are%20able%20to%20exercise%20decisive%20control%20over%20the%20trajectory%20of%20research%20by%20funding%20only%20select%20parts%20of%20a%20research%20project.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20fruits%20of%20public-funded%20research%20are%20placed%20at%20their%20disposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrabir%20Purkayastha%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20editor%20of%20NewsClick.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704890109000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F16173007%2FIMG_4643.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fknowledge-production-in-neo-liberal-times%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20output%20of%20scientific%20research%20no%20longer%20comprises%20research%20papers%20in%20journals%20that%20increase%20the%20boundaries%20of%20knowledge%2C%20but%20patents%20which%20can%20be%20turned%20into%20money.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fknowledge-production-in-neo-liberal-times%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boeing%20CEO%20Admits%20%E2%80%98Mistake%E2%80%99%2C%20Vows%20%E2%80%98Complete%20Transparency%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10175711%2Fimage-1718.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20Dave%20Calhoun%20took%20responsibility%20for%20last%20week%E2%80%99s%20mid-air%20blowout%20on%20an%20Alaska%20Airlines%20flight%2C%20vowing%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20transparency%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20aircraft%20maker%20grapples%20with%20the%20fallout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20approach%20this%20(by)%20number%20one%20acknowledging%20our%20mistake%2C%E2%80%9D%20Calhoun%20told%20employees%20at%20a%20safety%20meeting%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20is%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20first%20public%20acknowledgment%20of%20error%20since%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company-wide%20meeting%20was%20called%20after%20a%20plug%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fmissing-part-of-boeing-737-max-jet-found-in-backyard%2Fa-67913946%5C%22%3Eunused%20exit%20door%20seal%20blew%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20the%20plane%20was%20climbing%2C%20depressurising%20the%20aircraft%20at%2016%2C000%20feet%20(about%204.9%20kilometers).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%2C%20with%20the%20171%20passengers%20and%20six%20crew%20members%20on%20board%20made%20an%20emergency%20landing%20back%20to%20the%20Portland%20International%20Airport%20with%20no%20serious%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20(FAA)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ffaa-grounds-some-boeing-737-max-9-planes-after-mid-air-scare%2Fa-67905358%5C%22%3Egrounded%20all%20Boeing%20737%20Max%209%20aircrafts%20for%20inspection%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20to%20hundreds%20of%20canceled%20flights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVow%20of%20transparency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalhoun%20committed%20to%20working%20with%20the%20US%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20(NTSB)%20which%20is%20currently%20investigating%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20approach%20it%20with%20100%25%20and%20complete%20transparency%20every%20step%20of%20the%20way%2C%E2%80%9D%20Calhoun%20said%2C%20as%20per%20remarks%20released%20by%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NTSB%20is%20%E2%80%9Cas%20good%20as%20it%20gets%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CI%20trust%20every%20step%20they%20take%2C%20and%20they%20will%20get%20to%20a%20conclusion%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENTSB%20investigators%20on%20Monday%2C%20suggested%20that%20the%20part%20was%20not%20affixed%20adequately.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Alaska%20Airlines%20and%20United%20Airlines%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20two%20carriers%20which%20use%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20737%20Max%209%20planes%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funited-and-alaska-find-loose-bolts-on-boeing-737-max-9-planes%2Fa-67924547%5C%22%3Ereported%20loose%20hardware%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20some%20of%20their%20Boeing%20737%20Max%209%20planes%20during%20initial%20inspections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20on%20detailed%20inspection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20on%20Tuesday%20said%20it%20was%20still%20working%20with%20Boeing%20to%20finalise%20the%20detailed%20inspection%20instructions%20for%20grounded%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoeing%20offered%20an%20initial%20version%20of%20instructions%20yesterday%20which%20they%20are%20now%20revising%20because%20of%20feedback%20received%20in%20response%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20FAA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUpon%20receiving%20the%20revised%20version%20of%20instructions%20from%20Boeing%20the%20FAA%20will%20conduct%20a%20thorough%20review.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalhoun%20said%20the%20aviation%20giant%20was%20working%20with%20both%20regulators%20and%20airlines%20to%20ensure%20such%20an%20incident%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20never%20happen%20again.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fboeing-ceo-admits-mistake-vows-complete-transparency%2Fa-67934210%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EDW.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704889691000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10175711%2Fimage-1718.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fboeing-ceo-admits-mistake-vows-complete-transparency%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I