3EThe%20January%2022%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20will%20take%20place%20exactly%20at%20the%20same%20place%20in%20Ayodhya%20where%20the%20500-year-old%20Babri%20Mosque%20was%20demolished%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%20Ironically%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20while%20allowing%20construction%20of%20the%20temple%20on%20that%20spot%2C%20had%20held%20that%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20demolition%20was%20an%20egregious%20violation%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwami%20Vivekananda%2C%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20and%20%E2%80%93%20above%20all%20%E2%80%93%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20would%20have%20been%20deeply%20anguished%20and%20ashamed%20to%20see%20the%20lofty%20ideals%20they%20advocated%20now%20being%20contravened%20through%20the%20consecration%20of%20a%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20temple%20consecration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEighty-five%20years%20ago%2C%20on%20March%2018%2C%201939%2C%20Gandhi%20inaugurated%20the%20famous%20Lakshmi%20Narayan%20Temple%20(popularly%20known%20as%20the%20Birla%20Mandir)%20in%20Delhi%2C%20and%20explained%20to%20the%20huge%20crowd%20gathered%20there%20the%20meaning%20and%20significance%20of%20a%20temple%20in%20terms%20of%20respecting%20religious%20pluralism%20and%20rejecting%20communal%20hatred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20must%20be%20the%20daily%20prayer%20of%20every%20adherent%20of%20the%20Hindu%20faith%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gandhi%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20every%20known%20religion%20of%20the%20world%20should%20grow%20from%20day%20to%20day%20and%20should%20serve%20the%20whole%20of%20humanity.%E2%80%9D%20Explaining%20the%20significance%20of%20shrines%2C%20he%20fervently%20expressed%20optimism%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20hope%20that%20these%20temples%20will%20serve%20to%20propagate%20the%20idea%20of%20equal%20respect%20for%20religions%20and%20to%20make%20communal%20jealousies%20and%20strife%20things%20of%20the%20past.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20the%20%E2%80%9Cegregious%20violation%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20represented%20by%20demolishing%20the%20Babri%20Mosque%20and%20consecrating%20a%20temple%20in%20the%20exact%20same%20place%20%E2%80%93%20ever%20be%20in%20tune%20with%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20aforementioned%20vision%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVivekananda%E2%80%99s%20pride%20that%20Hindus%20built%20shrines%20for%20people%20of%20other%20faiths%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20before%20Gandhi%20articulated%20those%20lofty%20utterances%2C%20Vivekananda%20delivered%20a%20speech%20in%20Madras%20in%201897%20after%20returning%20from%20his%20historic%20visit%20to%20America%2C%20where%20he%20participated%20in%20the%20World%20Parliament%20of%20Religions%2C%20among%20other%20events.%20He%20took%20pride%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20here%20in%20India%20that%20Hindus%20have%20built%20and%20are%20still%20building%20churches%20for%20Christians%20and%20mosques%20for%20Mohammedans.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20he%20said%20represented%20the%20practical%20ideals%20of%20universal%20toleration%20and%20acceptance.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20went%20on%20to%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20world%20is%20waiting%20for%20this%20grand%20idea%20of%20universal%20toleration.%E2%80%9D%20He%20firmly%20asserted%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20civilisation%20can%20grow%20unless%20fanaticism%2C%20bloodshed%20and%20brutality%20stop.%20No%20civilisation%20can%20begin%20to%20lift%20up%20its%20head%20until%20we%20look%20charitably%20upon%20one%20another%3B%20and%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20that%20much-needed%20charity%20is%20to%20look%20charitably%20and%20kindly%20upon%20the%20religious%20conviction%20of%20others.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVivekananda%20proceeded%20further%3A%20%E2%80%9CNay%20more%2C%20to%20understand%20that%20not%20only%20should%20we%20be%20charitable%2C%20but%20also%20positively%20helpful%20to%20each%20other%2C%20however%20different%20our%20religious%20ideas%20and%20convictions%20may%20be.%20And%20that%20is%20exactly%20what%20we%20do%20in%20India%20as%20I%20have%20just%20related%20to%20you.%20It%20is%20here%20in%20India%20that%20Hindus%20have%20built%20and%20are%20still%20building%20churches%20for%20Christians%20and%20mosques%20for%20Mohammedans.%20That%20is%20the%20thing%20to%20do.%E2%80%9D%20These%20words%20form%20part%20of%20his%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchandigarh.rkmm.org%2FAKAM%2FBooks%2FLectures_from_Colombo_To_Almora.pdf%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fchandigarh.rkmm.org%2FAKAM%2FBooks%2FLectures_from_Colombo_To_Almora.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1704969029685000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0r6ILWBQetlDsAn0eNBA9d%5C%22%3ELectures%20from%20Colombo%20to%20Almora%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20controlling%20the%20state%20apparatus%20in%20India%20today%20often%20invoke%20Vivekananda.%20But%20they%20should%20be%20mindful%20of%20his%20stirring%20words%2C%20which%20assume%20greater%20relevance%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20forthcoming%20consecration%20and%20the%20mindless%20religious%20frenzy%20being%20generated%20all%20around%20that%20puts%20the%20values%20of%20religious%20tolerance%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETagore%E2%80%99s%20poem%20on%20a%20temple%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20Tagore%20been%20alive%20now%20to%20see%20the%20Ram%20Temple%E2%80%99s%20consecration%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENaya%3C%2Fem%3E%20Bharat%2C%20he%20would%20have%20recited%20his%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%98Deeno%20Daan%E2%80%99%2C%20composed%20in%201923.%20His%20rhythmic%20lines%20serve%20as%20a%20conscience-keeper%20for%20the%20nation%20and%20for%20Hinduism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20his%20poem%2C%20the%20poet%20interrogates%20a%20king%20through%20a%20saint%20and%20boldly%20denies%20the%20presence%20of%20God%20in%20a%20shrine%20consecrated%20by%20the%20king.%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20stanza%20is%20worth%20reproducing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20god%20in%20that%20temple%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20the%20Saint.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20King%20was%20enraged%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CNo%20God%3F%20Oh%20Saint%2C%20aren%E2%80%99t%20you%20speaking%20like%20an%20atheist%3F%3Cbr%3E%5CnOn%20the%20throne%20studded%20with%20priceless%20gems%2C%20beams%20the%20golden%20idol%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnAnd%20yet%2C%20you%20proclaim%20that%20it%20is%20empty%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20saint%20persisted%20in%20telling%20the%20truth%20and%20asserted%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20empty%3B%20rather%2C%20it%20is%20full%20of%20royal%20pride.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnYou%20have%20bestowed%20yourself%2C%20oh%20King%2C%20not%20the%20God%20of%20this%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20saint%20spoke%20the%20truth%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20anger%20and%20boastful%20claims%20that%20he%20spent%20two%20million%20gold%20coins%20in%20building%20the%20sky-high%20temple%20and%20consecrating%20it%20after%20performing%20all%20rituals.%20The%20saint%2C%20with%20composure%2C%20told%20the%20truth%20to%20the%20powerful%20king%20that%20the%20temple%20was%20built%20when%20millions%20suffered%20due%20to%20drought%20and%20became%20pauperised%20without%20food%20and%20shelter.%20The%20king%E2%80%99s%20empty%20religiosity%2C%20devoid%20of%20any%20traces%20of%20spirituality%2C%20enraged%20God%2C%20who%20responded%20by%20outlining%20the%20basic%20elements%20of%20his%20shrine.%20As%20Tagore%20puts%20it%20in%20his%20stanza%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20eternal%20home%20is%20lit%20by%20everlasting%20lamps%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20the%20midst%20of%20an%20azure%20sky%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20my%20home%20the%20foundations%20are%20built%20with%20the%20values%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnOf%20Truth%2C%20Peace%2C%20Compassion%20and%20Love.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20poverty-stricken%20puny%20miser%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnWho%20could%20not%20provide%20shelter%20to%20his%20own%20homeless%20subjects%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnDoes%20he%20really%20fancy%20he%20can%20give%20Me%20a%20home%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20enraged%20king%20banished%20the%20saint%20who%20upheld%20the%20true%20values%20rooted%20in%20charity%20and%20empathy%20to%20look%20upon%20all%20faiths%20as%20done%20by%20Vivekananda%2C%20and%20later%2C%20Gandhi.%20That%20is%20the%20true%20meaning%20of%20the%20consecration%20of%20a%20shrine%20or%20temple%20devoid%20of%20the%20pride%20and%20grandstanding%20of%20a%20ruler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20beyond%20the%20capacity%20of%20our%20rulers%20to%20learn%20these%20lessons%20from%20Vivekananda%2C%20Tagore%20and%20Gandhi%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20an%20officer%20on%20special%20duty%20to%20President%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704884453000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10162152%2Fimage-1716.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgandhi-vivekananda-tagore-and-temple-consecration%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Swami%20Vivekananda%2C%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20and%20%E2%80%93%20above%20all%20%E2%80%93%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20would%20have%20been%20deeply%20anguished%20and%20ashamed%20to%20see%20the%20lofty%20ideals%20they%20advocated%20now%20being%20contravened%20through%20the%20consecration%20of%20a%20temple.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgandhi-vivekananda-tagore-and-temple-consecration%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Brutal%20prison%20violence%2C%20a%20drug%20lord's%20escape%20and%20a%20nationwide%20curfew%20-%20what's%20happening%20in%20Ecuador%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704883860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-quito-ecuador_6416827.jpg%3F20240110075002%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbrutal-prison-violence-a-drug-lords-escape-and-a-nationwide-curfew-whats-happening-in-ecuador-13045249%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20brazen%20spectacle%20of%20hooded%20gunmen%20bursting%20onto%20a%20live%20TV%20set%20-%20as%20chaos%20rules%20in%20the%20country's%20prisons%20-%20has%20once%20again%20thrown%20Ecuador's%20security%20crisis%20into%20the%20spotlight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbrutal-prison-violence-a-drug-lords-escape-and-a-nationwide-curfew-whats-happening-in-ecuador-13045249%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbrutal-prison-violence-a-drug-lords-escape-and-a-nationwide-curfew-whats-happening-in-ecuador-13045249%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbrutal-prison-violence-a-drug-lords-escape-and-a-nationwide-curfew-whats-happening-in-ecuador-13045249%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20'Illegal'%20Ways%20of%20Law-Making%20by%20India's%20Parliament%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15091225%2Fdownload-13.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202024%20was%20ushered%20in%20with%20the%20news%20that%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20laws%2C%20passed%20by%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20only%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw%2Fstory%2Fnew-criminal-code-laws-passed-parliament-challenged-supreme-court-2482902-2024-01-01%5C%22%3Echallenged%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Notably%2C%20according%20to%20media%20reports%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fpetition-filed-in-supreme-court-against-new-criminal-laws-passed-by-parliament%2Farticleshow%2F106456095.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Epetition%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Bills%20were%20%E2%80%9Cenacted%20without%20any%20parliamentary%20debate%E2%80%9D%20as%20most%20Opposition%20MPs%20were%20suspended.%20Earlier%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202023%20was%20also%20challenged%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20petition%20challenging%20the%20Act%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2Fretired-civil-servants-challenge-forest-conservation-act-amendments-sc%5C%22%3Ealleged%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Joint%20Parliament%20Committee%20(JPC)%20which%20was%20set%20up%20to%20study%2C%20analyse%2C%20and%20report%20on%20the%20Bill%20ignored%20most%20of%20the%201309%20memoranda%20it%20had%20received%20which%20were%20critical%20of%20the%20Bill.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20pre-legislative%20consultation%20process%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-environment-law-ministries-2023-amendments-forest-conservation-act-240689%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Echallenged%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommon%20between%20these%20two%20petitions%20is%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20legislative%20procedure%20and%20questions%20raised%20on%20the%20egregious%20ways%20in%20which%20laws%20were%20made.%20But%20is%20legislative%20procedure%20open%20to%20judicial%20review%3F%20The%20law%20on%20this%20is%20not%20settled%20and%20the%20jurisprudence%20is%20still%20evolving%2C%20which%20makes%20these%20petitions%20both%20risky%20and%20exciting.%3Cu%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJudicial%20review%20versus%20the%20theory%20of%20exclusive%20cognisance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20form%20of%20government%20is%20modeled%20on%20the%20British%20parliamentary%20system%2C%20not%20all%20features%20were%20inherited.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20written%20constitution%2C%20the%20British%20model%20was%20one%20of%20%E2%80%98parliamentary%20sovereignty%E2%80%99%20in%20which%20the%20legislature%20i.e.%20the%20British%20Parliament%20is%20the%20supreme%20lawmaking%20authority%20and%20the%20courts%20did%20not%20have%20the%20mandate%20or%20power%20to%20strike%20down%20a%20law%20made%20by%20parliament%20if%20it%20violated%20people%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20The%20Indian%20model%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20is%20one%20of%20constitutional%20supremacy%2C%20where%20each%20institution%2C%20including%20the%20Indian%20parliament%2C%20functions%20within%20the%20limits%20of%20its%20powers%20set%20by%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20Therefore%2C%20any%20law%20made%20by%20it%20can%20be%20struck%20down%20by%20courts%20if%20it%20violates%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20other%20constitutional%20rights%20of%20the%20people%2C%20or%20other%20provisions%20of%20the%20constitution.%20In%20the%20famed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjudgments.ecourts.gov.in%2FKBJ%2F%3Fp%3Dhome%2Fintro%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKesavanand%20Bharti%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%2C%20it%20was%20held%20that%20judicial%20review%20%E2%80%9Cis%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20our%20constitutional%20system%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20as%20there%20are%20limits%20to%20what%20the%20parliament%20can%20do%2C%20there%20are%20limits%20on%20the%20power%20of%20judicial%20review%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticles%20122%20and%20212%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20impose%20one%20such%20limitation.%20These%20Articles%20provide%20that%20the%20validity%20of%20any%20proceeding%20in%20parliament%20and%20legislature%20of%20any%20state%2C%20respectively%2C%20will%20not%20be%20called%20into%20question%20in%20any%20court%20of%20law%20on%20grounds%20of%20%E2%80%98irregularity%20of%20procedure%E2%80%99.%20There%20is%20no%20guidance%20available%20in%20the%20constitution%20on%20what%20is%20an%20%E2%80%98irregularity%20of%20procedure%E2%80%99.%20These%20Articles%20are%20based%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ferskinemay.parliament.uk%2Fsection%2F4543%2Fcontrol-of-proceedings%5C%22%3Eexclusive%20cognisance%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20inherited%20from%20the%20British%20parliament%2C%20according%20to%20which%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20have%20the%20right%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20sole%20judge%20of%20the%20lawfulness%20of%20their%20own%20proceedings%20and%20to%20settle%20%E2%80%93%20or%20depart%20from%20%E2%80%93%20their%20own%20codes%20of%20procedures%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%2C%20there%20exists%20a%20tension%20between%20the%20mandate%20of%20judicial%20review%20and%20the%20limitations%20under%20Articles%20122%20and%20212.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20have%20the%20courts%20resolved%20this%20tension%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20bar%20under%20Articles%20122%20and%20212%2C%20petitions%20challenging%20legislative%20procedure%20have%20reached%20the%20courts%20on%20many%20occasions%20and%20courts%20have%20found%20a%20way%20to%20carve%20out%20a%20scope%20for%20judicial%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalfreedomofexpression.columbia.edu%2Fcases%2Fputtaswamy-v-union-of-india-ii%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%20II%20%3C%2Fem%3Ejudgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Aadhaar%20judgment)%2C%20the%20certification%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20Bill%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20as%20a%20Money%20Bill%20was%20challenged%2C%20among%20other%20challenges.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20both%20the%20majority%20and%20minority%20judgments%20concurred%20in%20holding%20that%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Speaker%20to%20certify%20a%20Bill%20as%20a%20Money%20Bill%20was%20open%20to%20judicial%20review.%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20in%20his%20minority%20judgment%2C%20further%20elaborated%20on%20this%20and%20said%20that%20the%20theory%20of%20exclusive%20cognisance%20finds%20no%20applicability%20in%20India.%20Article%20122%20cannot%20and%20does%20not%20completely%20bar%20judicial%20review%20of%20legislative%20procedure.%20It%20was%20further%20held%20that%20this%20Article%20only%20prevents%20%E2%80%98irregularity%20of%20procedure%E2%80%99%20from%20being%20questioned%2C%20but%20not%20the%20%E2%80%98illegality%20of%20procedure%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20distinction%20between%20irregularity%20and%20illegality%20of%20procedure%20found%20one%20of%20its%20first%20mentions%20in%20%3Cem%3ESpecial%20Reference%20No.1%20of%201964%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20pressed%20into%20service%20by%20the%20President%20of%20India%20for%20an%20advisory%20opinion%20on%20a%20question%20of%20privilege%20of%20a%20legislative%20assembly.%20In%20its%20opinion%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20if%20any%20proceeding%20of%20the%20legislature%20is%20alleged%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20or%20unconstitutional%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20%E2%80%9Cmerely%20irregular%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20procedure%2C%20then%20it%20can%20be%20scrutinised%20by%20a%20court%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20when%20does%20a%20proceeding%20become%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%E2%80%9D%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20remains%20an%20open%20question%2C%20both%20of%20law%20and%20fact.%20A%20basic%20analysis%20of%20some%20judgments%20rendered%20on%20this%20subject%20points%20to%20a%20possible%20distinction%20between%20violation%20of%20internal%20rules%20and%20procedures%20of%20parliament%20and%20violation%20of%20a%20constitutional%20provision.%20The%20former%20could%20be%20a%20mere%20%E2%80%98irregularity%E2%80%99%20but%20the%20latter%20could%20be%20an%20%E2%80%98illegality%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20have%20been%20judgments%20where%20violation%20of%20non-codified%20conventions%20has%20been%20held%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%202020%2C%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20was%20petitioned%20against%20the%20nomination%20of%20an%20MLA%20as%20a%20Chairperson%20of%20the%20Public%20Accounts%20Committee%20in%20the%20West%20Bengal%20Legislative%20Assembly%2C%20against%20the%20set%20precedents%20and%20conventions.%20In%20this%20judgment%20(%3Cem%3EAmbika%20Roy%20v.%20The%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Speaker%2C%20West%20Bengal%20Legislative%20Assembly%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E)%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20high%20court%20held%20that%20violation%20of%20the%20convention%2C%20though%20not%20laid%20down%20in%20any%20rule%20of%20procedure%2C%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9Cillegality%20committed%E2%80%9D%20and%20Article%20212%20did%20not%20bar%20the%20Court%20from%20reviewing%20it.%3Cu%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20lawmakers%20themselves%20not%20bound%20by%20any%20law%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20open%20question%20of%20when%20a%20legislative%20proceeding%20becomes%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20raises%20many%20more%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20the%20internal%20rules%20and%20procedures%20of%20the%20House%20not%20%E2%80%98law%E2%80%99%20that%20their%20violation%20will%20not%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%3F%20Are%20the%20lawmakers%20themselves%20not%20bound%20by%20any%20%E2%80%98law%E2%80%99%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20lawmaking%3F%20If%20these%20rules%20of%20procedure%20are%20not%20binding%2C%20can%20be%20followed%20when%20convenient%20and%20can%20be%20violated%20at%20will%2C%20why%20do%20these%20rules%20exist%20at%20all%3F%20It%20must%20be%20remembered%20that%20under%20Article%20118%2C%20the%20constitution%20empowers%20each%20House%20of%20Parliament%20to%20frame%20their%20own%20rules%20and%20procedures%20but%20these%20are%20subject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20constitution.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20substance%20of%20the%20rules%20themselves%20can%20be%20challenged%20if%20they%20violate%20the%20constitution.%20Then%20how%20can%20the%20violation%20of%20these%20rules%20not%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98unconstitutional%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20not%20just%20the%20codified%20rules%20of%20procedures%2C%20the%20Houses%20are%20equally%20bound%20by%20precedents%20and%20conventions.%20But%20these%20are%20also%20routinely%20violated.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20rules%20of%20procedure%20do%20not%20categorically%20provide%20that%20Bills%20must%20be%20mandatorily%20referred%20to%20Parliament%20Committees%20before%20they%20are%20taken%20up%20for%20debate%2C%20but%20a%20healthy%20convention%20existed%20of%20sending%20Bills%20to%20Committees%20for%20scrutiny.%20As%20per%20data%20gathered%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fparliament%2Fsession_track%2F2023%2Fvital_stats%2FVital_Stats_Winter_Session_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EPRS%20Legislative%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%2015%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Lok%20Sabha%20set%20a%20precedent%20of%20sending%2071%25%20of%20all%20Bills%20to%20Parliament%20Committees%2C%20but%20for%20the%20current%2017%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0Lok%20Sabha%2C%20this%20stands%20at%2016%25%20of%20Bills%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20three%20Criminal%20Bills%2C%20technically%20no%20codified%20rule%20was%20violated%2C%20by%20passing%20these%20Bills%20when%20many%20MPs%20were%20under%20suspension.%20But%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20such%20an%20undemocratic%20way%20of%20passing%20Bills%20militate%20against%20the%20Preamble%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20recognises%20India%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98democracy%E2%80%99%20and%20guarantees%20%E2%80%98political%20justice%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98liberty%20of%20thought%20and%20expression%E2%80%99%3F%20When%20a%20section%20of%20elected%20representatives%20are%20unable%20to%20voice%20their%20opinions%2C%20consenting%20or%20dissenting%2C%20to%20the%20making%20of%20any%20law%2C%20why%20should%20that%20not%20be%20held%20as%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98unconstitutional%E2%80%99%3F%20%3Cu%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20ways%20of%20making%20laws%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20many%20instances%20where%20Bills%20were%20pushed%20through%20parliament%20in%20violation%20of%20rules%20of%20procedure%2C%20conventions%20and%20all%20manners%20of%20propriety.%20In%202017%2C%20the%20Enemy%20Property%20(Amendment%20and%20Validation)%20Bill%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Fvantage%2Fgovernment-subverted-procedure-good-faith-passing-enemy-property-bill%5C%22%3Epassed%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20most%20Opposition%20MPs%20had%20left%20on%20the%20assurance%20that%20the%20Bill%20would%20not%20be%20taken%20up%20on%20that%20day.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Bill%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fengage%2Farticle%2Fdiminishing-role-parliament-case-jammu-and-kashmir%5C%22%3Esprung%20as%20a%20complete%20surprise%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20pushed%20through%20Rajya%20Sabha%20without%20affording%20MPs%20any%20opportunity%20to%20read%20or%20analyse%20the%20Bill.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Farm%20Bills%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.firstpost.com%2Findia%2Fwho-controls-parliament-instead-of-building-a-robust-system-we-have-bled-its-vitality-dignity-and-efficacy-8840041.html%5C%22%3Ecleared%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20through%20voice%20vote%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20intense%20protests%2C%20as%20MPs%E2%80%99%20call%20for%20division%20(recorded%20vote)%20on%20the%20question%20of%20sending%20the%20Bills%20to%20a%20Select%20Committee%20was%20being%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2017%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Lok%20Sabha%20also%20paints%20a%20shameful%20picture%20of%20pushing%20Bills%20through%20either%20amid%20intense%20protests%20or%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20Opposition%2C%20in%20session%20after%20session.%20As%20per%20my%20own%20research%2C%20in%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%20of%202020%2C%20as%20Opposition%20MPs%20boycotted%20proceedings%20following%20the%20Farm%20Bill%20fiasco%2C%20for%2015%20of%20the%2027%20Bills%20passed%20in%20that%20session%2C%20Opposition%20MPs%20were%20absent%20in%20either%20or%20both%20Houses.%20In%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%20of%202021%2C%20as%20Opposition%20protested%20because%20the%20government%20stonewalled%20their%20demand%20for%20debate%20on%20the%20Pegasus%20snooping%20scandal%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protest%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20cleared%2018%20Bills%20amid%20protests%2C%20spending%20an%20average%20of%20only%2015%20minutes%20on%20each.%20In%20the%20just%20concluded%20Winter%20Session%20of%202023%2C%20after%20the%20unprecedented%20suspension%20of%20146%20MPs%20from%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20for%20demanding%20discussion%20on%20Parliament%20security%20breach%2C%2014%20Bills%20were%20cleared%20by%20one%20or%20both%20Houses%20within%203%20days%20in%20which%20the%20Opposition%20either%20did%20not%20participate%20or%20there%20was%20minimal%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInternal%20checks%20have%20failed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20these%20egregious%20ways%20in%20which%20Bills%20are%20being%20passed%2C%20be%20brushed%20under%20the%20carpet%2C%20by%20terming%20these%20as%20mere%20%E2%80%98irregularity%20of%20procedure%E2%80%99%3F%20It%20is%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20in%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%20imagination%2C%20legislature%20generally%20and%20specifically%2C%20the%20opposition%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20keep%20the%20executive%20under%20check.%20However%2C%20as%20I%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frepository.nls.ac.in%2Fslr%2Fvol18%2Fiss1%2F2%2F%5C%22%3Eargued%20here%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20government%20tightly%20controlling%20agenda%20setting%2C%20parliament%20is%20virtually%20powerless%20to%20enforce%20rules%20of%20procedures.%20Internal%20checks%20having%20failed%2C%20it%20is%20either%20the%20court%20of%20people%20or%20the%20court%20of%20law%20which%20can%20deter%20the%20government%20from%20making%20laws%20in%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMaansi%20Verma%20is%20a%20lawyer%2C%20public%20policy%20researcher%2C%20and%20Founder%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EMaadhyam%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%93%20a%20civic%20engagement%20initiative%20bringing%20Parliament%20and%20policy-making%20closer%20to%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704882655000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15091225%2Fdownload-13.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-illegal-ways-of-law-making-by-indias-parliament%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20government%20tightly%20controlling%20agenda%20setting%2C%20parliament%20is%20virtually%20powerless%20to%20enforce%20rules%20of%20procedures.%20Internal%20checks%20having%20failed%2C%20it%20is%20either%20the%20court%20of%20people%20or%20the%20court%20of%20law%20which%20can%20deter%20the%20government%20from%20making%20laws%20in%20'illegal'%20ways.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-illegal-ways-of-law-making-by-indias-parliament%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Norway%20becomes%20first%20country%20to%20back%20controversial%20deep%20sea%20mining%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704882600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-deep-sea-arctic_6417217.jpg%3F20240110131504%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnorway-becomes-first-country-to-back-controversial-deep-sea-mining-13045241%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Controversial%20deep%20sea%20mining%20is%20one%20step%20closer%20to%20reality%20as%20Norway%20approved%20the%20practice%20in%20a%20parliamentary%20vote%2C%20sparking%20furious%20outcry%20from%20environmental%20campaigners.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A48%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnorway-becomes-first-country-to-back-controversial-deep-sea-mining-13045241%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.s